y as the business grows, improved customer satisfaction, and easy reporting and tracking features.\"", "\"BIG DATA\":\"Big data refers to vast data sets that may be analyzed to reveal patterns, trends, and associations, especially relating to human behavior and interactions. Essential characteristics of big data include volume, variety, velocity, veracity, and value.\"", "\"STRUCTURED DATA\":\"Structured data is data stored within defined fields within a defined record, along with similar data, according to the specifications laid down in a data model. The data model limits the data collected and how it can be processed.\"", "\"UNSTRUCTURED DATA\":\"Unstructured data is information gathered in various forms and ways, not in accordance with any data model, and thus may be difficult to store or analyze.\"", "\"CHARACTERISTICS OF BIG DATA\":\"The essential characteristics of big data include volume (a tremendous amount), variety (non-uniform, from internal and external sources), velocity (fast and continuous processing), veracity (validity and reliability of data), and value (cost-benefit analysis of big data).\"", "\"DATA ANALYTICS\":\"Data Analytics\" is the processing of big data to identify trends, patterns, and associations, and to transform data into a visual context. It involves various techniques such as data testing, data mining, predictive analytics, text analytics, and statistical analytics. The primary goal of data analytics is to identify patterns, relationships, and trends within data to inform decision-making.", "\"DATA TESTING\":\"Data testing involves testing models or hypotheses on existing data to validate assumptions and predictions.\"", "\"DATA MINING\":\"Data mining involves analyzing data to identify patterns, relationships, and correlations. It includes finding relationships between variables, applying known structures to new data, identifying groups and structures within the data, spotting unusual items, and providing results in a user-friendly form.\"", "\"PREDICTIVE ANALYTICS\":\"Predictive analytics is a type of data mining that uses statistical or machine learning techniques to predict future events, such as the likelihood that a customer may be persuaded to buy a more expensive product.\"", "\"TEXT ANALYTICS\":\"Text analytics involves scanning emails and word documents to extract useful information, such as keywords that indicate an interest in a product. Voice analytics is a similar process but with audio data.\"", "\"STATISTICAL ANALYTICS\":\"Statistical analytics is used to identify trends, correlations, and changes in behavior within data.\"", "\"BIG DATA (DIKW) PYRAMID\":\"The Big Data (DIKW) Pyramid, developed by Ackoff and further by Jennifer Rowley, shows the stages of transforming initial unstructured data into material for reliable decision-making and accurate forecasting. The stages are Data, Information, Knowledge, and Wisdom.\""], "parameters": {"model": "text-embedding-3-small", "temperature": 0.0, "frequency_penalty": null, "presence_penalty": null, "top_p": 1.0, "max_tokens": 4000, "n": 1}}